# espeak-ng dictionary source for chemistry/biology pronunciation
#
# Format: each non-comment line is a `.replace` directive that rewrites
# the source token to a TTS-friendly form, which espeak-ng then phonemizes
# normally.
#
# This file is the source-of-truth for plugin v0.14.1+. Until compiled and
# wired into Piper, the regex + AI passes in reader.js handle expansion
# client-side. New terms added here should also be considered for the regex
# table in chemPreprocess() until espeak takes over.
#
# ─── ESPEAK-NG COMPILER (step 2 findings, plugin v0.14.3) ─────────────
#
# Latest release: 1.52.0  (https://github.com/espeak-ng/espeak-ng)
# Windows asset: espeak-ng.msi
#   https://github.com/espeak-ng/espeak-ng/releases/download/1.52.0/espeak-ng.msi
#
# Caveat: only an MSI installer is shipped, no portable zip. Two paths:
#   (a) Run installer once on dev machine, then `espeak-ng --compile=en`
#       inside a dir containing the upstream en `dictsource/` files plus
#       this chem.list appended. Output: en_dict (binary).
#   (b) For per-user plugin install: extract MSI with `msiexec /a … /qb
#       TARGETDIR=…` to get the espeak-ng binaries portably, OR use
#       lessmsi/7-zip to extract.
#
# Recommended approach for the plugin: precompile a supplemental dict on a
# dev machine, bake the resulting binary into the XPI, copy it into Piper's
# espeak-ng-data dir at install time. No runtime compilation needed.
#
# Upstream en dictsource (needed alongside chem.list during compile):
#   https://github.com/espeak-ng/espeak-ng/tree/master/dictsource

.replace
# Chiral / stereo descriptors
d.r.        d r
d.r         d r
e.e.        e e
e.e         e e
e.r.        e r
e.r         e r

